            <div id="corona-intro">
                <h3>
                    What is COVID-19?
                </h3>
                <div>
                    Coronavirus disease or COVID-19 is an infectious disease caused by a newly discovered
                    coronavirus. It is caused by SARS-CoV-2 that can trigger what doctors call a respiratory tract
                    infection. It can affect your upper respiratory tract (sinuses, nose, and throat) or lower
                    respiratory tract (windpipe and lungs). It spreads the same way other coronaviruses do,
                    mainly through person-to-person contact. Infections range from mild to deadly.
                </div>
